Key Match Events: Pakistani captain Babar Azam praised the team's bowling but acknowledged the batting issues.
Shaheen Afridi bowled superbly at the top of Ireland's innings.
Shaheen Afridi hit a six to win the game for Pakistan with seven balls to spare.
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan captain Babar Azam stated, 'We have a good bunch of players. Let’s go home and see where we’ve lacked, where we’re not good enough.'
Ireland captain Paul Stirling said, 'We played in patches. We didn't start the day terribly well and they put pressure on us early on. I think that was the difference in the end.'
Andrew Leonard, an Irish cricket commentator, mentioned, 'I really don't think it's indicative of where the Irish men's team is at the moment.'
Daniel Norcross, a BBC Test Match Special commentator, noted, 'This was a difficult group, a sort of group of death and Ireland have come out of it with nothing.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan won by three wickets with seven balls to spare.
Abbas Afridi was dropped on six during the Pakistan innings.
Shaheen Afridi's performance was crucial for Pakistan's victory.
